1. The logged hello router is the same HTTP router as hello_router, with one addition: per-request audit logging.
2. For a GET request to the root path, the router returns HTTP 200 with a greeting body.
3. For a GET request to /ping, the router returns HTTP 200 with the body "pong".
4. For any other request, the router returns HTTP 404 with the body "not found".
5. For every incoming request the service appends a line to /tmp/verbose_router.log recording the method and path of the request.
6. The service listens on port 18890 and reads up to 4096 bytes per incoming request.
